%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20alerted%20New%20York%20City%20employees%20on%20Sunday%20that%20affected%20areas%20of%20its%20Chelsea%20campus%20were%20undergoing%20bedbug%20treatment.%3Cp%3ETim%20Clayton%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-new-york-city-google-property-chelsea-market-2018-2%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20Chelsea%20campus%3C%2Fa%3E%20underwent%20bedbug%20treatment%20over%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20pest-control%20company%20said%20bedbug%20sightings%20in%20commercial%20spaces%20have%20increased%20as%20employees%20return%20to%20offices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBedbugs%20pose%20an%20icky%20problem%20for%20employers%2C%20who%20should%20have%20protocols%20in%20place%20to%20avoid%20legal%20issues.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20workers%20are%20heading%20into%20the%20office%20with%20laptops%2C%20lattes%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20bedbugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20sent%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20memo%20over%20the%20weekend%20informing%20New%20York%20City%20employees%20that%20it%20was%20treating%20its%20Chelsea%20campus%20offices%20for%20the%20pests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20Real%20Estate%20%26amp%3B%20Workplace%20Services%20team%20%26quot%3Bwas%20recently%20informed%20of%20a%20possible%20bed%20bug%20issue%20at%20our%20Chelsea%20campus%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Sunday%20memo%2C%20acquired%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BToday%2C%20exterminators%20inspected%20the%20NYC-9TH%2C%20Chelsea%20Market%2C%208510%2C%20and%20Pier%2057%20buildings%20with%20a%20sniffer%20dog%20and%20found%20credible%20evidence%20of%20their%20presence.%20Initial%20treatment%20has%20been%20completed%20on%20the%20affected%20floors%20of%20the%20Chelsea%20campus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20of%20Google's%20bedbug%20memo%20was%20earlier%20reported%20by%20Wired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20time%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20workers%20logging%20on%20from%20home%20didn't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20creepy-crawlies%20in%20their%20cubicles.%20Now%2C%20as%20more%20employees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20bedbugs%20are%20coming%20along%20for%20the%20ride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20what%20we%20tend%20to%20call%20'take-your-bedbug-to-work%20events%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Gil%20Bloom%2C%20an%20entomologist%20who%20is%20president%20of%20Standard%20Pest%20Management%20in%20New%20York.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20primarily%20hitchhiking%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20from%20home%20environments%26quot%3B%20via%20items%20like%20backpacks%20and%20clothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBedbug%20issues%20in%20New%20York%20haven't%20reached%20the%20level%20they%20were%20prior%20to%20the%20pandemic%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there's%20been%20an%20uptick%20in%20sightings%20at%20commercial%20locations%20since%20life%20began%20returning%20to%20normal%2C%20Bloom%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223a51844b-540b-4cda-ad9a-e151378e55e2%5C%22%3EOffices%20aren't%20immune%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20isn't%20the%20only%20employer%20to%20deal%20with%20this%20issue.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20bedbugs%20were%20discovered%20at%20the%20Ohio%20Bureau%20of%20Workers'%20Compensation%20office%2C%20and%20staff%20from%20the%20affected%20area%20had%20to%20leave%20while%20the%20building%20underwent%20treatment%2C%20the%20Columbus%20Dispatch%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buzzfeednews.com%2Farticle%2Fdavidmack%2Fbugsfeed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuzzFeed's%20Manhattan%20headquarters%3C%2Fa%3E%20similarly%20had%20to%20get%20bedbug%20treatment.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturkish-airlines-passengers-encountered-bedbugs-three-flights-report-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHotels%20and%20airlines%20have%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20wingless%20insects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20York%20City%20ranked%20second%20among%20the%20most%20bedbug-infested%20cities%20in%202018%2C%20dropped%20to%20fifth%20place%20in%202021%2C%20and%20climbed%20to%20third%20in%202023%2C%20based%20on%20data%20from%20300%20Terminix%20branches%20in%20the%20US.%20As%20of%20June%2C%20New%20York%20is%20back%20in%20second%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloom%20said%20when%20companies%20suspect%20bedbugs%20are%20in%20a%20workspace%2C%20exterminators%20typically%20bring%20in%20detection%20dogs%20to%20confirm%20their%20existence%20and%20identify%20affected%20areas.%20While%20an%20employee%20might%20accidentally%20bring%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebedbugs%20into%20work%2C%20offices%20usually%20lack%20the%20ideal%20infrastructure%20for%20the%20insects%20to%20settle%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20great%20hotspot%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloom%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20beds%20in%20most%20offices.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20like%20finding%20a%20bedbug%20in%20a%20haystack.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIdentifying%20the%20location%20of%20the%20outbreak%20allows%20companies%20to%20narrow%20down%20the%20treatment%20area%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-seems-like-bedbugs-but-arent-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eresolve%20the%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Bloom%20said.%20He%20describes%20such%20instances%20as%20%26quot%3Bintroductions%2C%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20full-blown%20%26quot%3Binfestations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2299fa441b-3f05-4a1a-8df5-7a147e79ffc9%5C%22%3EA%20liability%20issue%20for%20companies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20bedbugs%20might%20be%20unpleasant%2C%20Jerome%20Goddard%2C%20a%20medical%20entomologist%20at%20Mississippi%20State%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20there%20is%20little%20to%20no%20transmission%20of%20disease%20from%20the%20pests.%20Often%2C%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20is%20dealing%20with%20the%20ick%20factor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20effects%20are%20emotional%20and%20psychological%2C%26quot%3B%20Goddard%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I'm%20not%20saying%20that's%20not%20real.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%2C%20however%2C%20could%20face%20legal%20consequences%20if%20they%20don't%20take%20steps%20to%20kill%20the%20bugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20have%20a%20duty%20to%20provide%20a%20safe%20workplace%20per%20OSHA%20requirements%2C%20and%20failing%20to%20protect%20workers%20could%20create%20a%20liability%2C%20said%20Andrea%20Whalen%2C%20a%20senior%20HR%20business%20strategist%20at%20consulting%20firm%20Clark%20Schaefer%20Strategic%20HR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloom%20said%20companies%20don't%20usually%20provide%20extermination%20services%20to%20individual%20employees%20unless%20there's%20a%20repeat%20situation%20and%20the%20office%20is%20trying%20to%20find%20the%20source%20to%20avoid%20future%20introductions%20to%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhalen%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20companies%20should%20establish%20clear%2C%20written%20rules%20that%20cover%20different%20kinds%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-if-you-have-bedbugs-paris-infestation-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einfestations%20or%20outbreaks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Those%20policies%20could%20include%20considerations%20about%20paying%20workers%20if%20they%20have%20to%20be%20sent%20home%20while%20pest-control%20professionals%20treat%20a%20worksite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20employees%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bmoral%20and%20an%20ethical%20responsibility%26quot%3B%20to%20tell%20their%20employers%20if%20they%20have%20bedbugs%2C%20policies%20should%20include%20a%20way%20for%20employees%20to%20report%20an%20issue%20confidentially%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20a%20way%20for%20an%20employee%20to%20come%20forward%20and%20say%2C%20'I%20have%20this%20issue%2C'%20so%20that%20it%20protects%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20Whalen%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20should%20be%20addressed%20with%20%26quot%3Bempathy%20and%20discretion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20she%20said%2C%20places%20where%20people%20often%20think%20of%20outbreaks%20occurring%20%E2%80%94%20like%20hotels%2C%20schools%2C%20and%20hospitals%20%E2%80%94%20are%20themselves%20workplaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can%20happen%20to%20anyone%2C%26quot%3B%20Whalen%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20happen%20to%20any%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20We%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Reach%20out%20to%20the%20reporters%20via%20email%20at%20aaltchek%40insider.com%20and%20tparadis%40insider.com%2C%20or%20via%20the%20secure%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20aalt.19%20or%20tparadis.70.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbedbugs-following-workers-back-to-office-google-campus-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1761126301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f7aeea1c1f80efbec5f81a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbedbugs-following-workers-back-to-office-google-campus-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Google's%20Chelsea%20campus%20in%20New%20York%20City%20was%20treated%20for%20bedbugs%20recently.%20As%20more%20workers%20head%20back%20to%20offices%2C%20pests%20are%20coming%20along%20for%20the%20ride.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek%2CTim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbedbugs-following-workers-back-to-office-google-campus-2025-10%22%2C