ecarious%20time%20for%20junior%20venture%20capitalists.%20Many%20came%20of%20age%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftotal-global-us-venture-capital-funding-in-2021-broke-records-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrothy%3C%2Fa%3E%20post-pandemic%20boom%2C%20when%20deal%20flow%20was%20brisk%2C%20valuations%20soared%2C%20and%20portfolio%20companies%20seemed%20to%20double%20in%20value%20every%20few%20months.%20Then%20the%20market%20cooled%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-fears-exctinction-event-startup-failure-rate-increase-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efunds%20pulled%20back%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuddenly%2C%20midlevel%20investors%20had%20fewer%20chances%20to%20prove%20themselves%2C%20and%20some%20of%20their%20once-glittering%20deals%20now%20looked%20painfully%20overpriced.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-investors-face-tougher-path-to-promotion-partner-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epath%20to%20partnership%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20already%20murky%2C%20became%20even%20narrower.%20Some%20disillusioned%20investors%20left%20the%20industry%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202022%2C%20Rechtman%20assumed%20he'd%20eventually%20leave%20Slow%20to%20raise%20his%20own%20fund.%20Plans%20changed%2C%20and%20not%2C%20he%20says%2C%20because%20the%20market%20soured.%20Through%20September%2C%2068%20debut%20funds%20closed%2C%20versus%20183%20in%20all%20of%20last%20year%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpitchbook.com%2Fnews%2Freports%2Fq3-2025-pitchbook-nvca-venture-monitor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPitchBook%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Emerging%20managers%20are%20also%20taking%20twice%20as%20long%20to%20raise%20their%20next%20funds%20%E2%80%94%20a%20headwind%20that%20would%20give%20any%20investor%20pause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERechtman%20says%20he's%20staying%20for%20a%20simpler%20reason.%20The%20job's%20not%20finished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%2C%20Slow%20general%20partner%20and%20early%20Facebook%20executive%20Sam%20Lessin%20gave%20Rechtman%20this%20advice%3A%20%26quot%3BFish%20in%20waters%20where%20other%20firms%20aren't%20fishing.%26quot%3B%20Rechtman%20took%20it%20somewhat%20literally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20he%20grabbed%20a%20last-minute%20flight%20to%20Tampa%20to%20reconnect%20with%20a%20startup%20billing%20itself%20as%20%26quot%3BUber%20for%20heavy-equipment%20repair.%26quot%3B%20Founded%20in%202020%2C%20Heave%20has%20quietly%20assembled%20a%20network%20that%20it%20claims%20covers%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20the%20country's%20heavy-machinery%20mechanics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERechtman%20closed%20a%20handshake%20deal%20with%20the%20founder%20over%20smoked%20fish%2C%20and%20Slow%20joined%20its%20%247%20million%20seed%20round%2C%20which%20was%20announced%20in%20August.%20It's%20the%20kind%20of%20off-beat%2C%20unsexy%20bet%20that%20has%20become%20Rechtman's%20calling%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20approach%20has%20nudged%20Slow%20into%20areas%20it%20might%20have%20otherwise%20overlooked%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-16-rising-star-investors-healthcare-venture-capital-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20growth%20buyouts%2C%20and%20what%20Rechtman%20calls%20%26quot%3Breal-world%20businesses.%26quot%3B%20This%20spring%2C%20Slow%20backed%20SuperDial%2C%20which%20builds%20voice%20agents%20for%20healthcare%20organizations%20and%20has%20already%20handled%20more%20than%201%20million%20calls.%20Colleran%20said%20Rechtman%20also%20worked%20with%20him%20to%20close%20Journey%2C%20a%20travel%20rewards%20platform%20created%20by%20Brian%20Kelly%2C%20founder%20of%20The%20Points%20Guy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlow%20doesn't%20vote%20by%20unanimity.%20It%20runs%20on%20a%20simple%20rule%3A%20any%20two%20partners%20can%20greenlight%20a%20deal.%20Decision-making%20power%20is%20flat.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20