the%20new%20housing-market%20winners%20could%20stay%20on%20top%20for%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20move%20in%20predictable%20patterns.%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%20the%20Northeast%20and%20Midwest%20hemorrhaged%20people%20to%20the%20Sun%20Belt%2C%20where%20jobs%20were%20plentiful%2C%20the%20weather%20balmier%2C%20and%20homes%20cheaper.%20Between%20mid-2018%20and%20mid-2019%2C%20the%20last%20full%20year%20of%20Census%20data%20before%20the%20pandemic%20set%20in%2C%20the%20Northeast%20lost%20a%20net%20294%2C000%20residents%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20while%20the%20Midwest%20lost%20nearly%20162%2C000.%20The%20South%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20gained%20almost%20408%2C000%20people%2C%20and%20the%20West%20saw%20an%20uptick%20of%2048%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20moving%20from%20the%20North%20to%20the%20South%20for%20many%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Simonsen%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20build%20the%20houses%20in%20the%20South.%20We%20sell%20our%20homes%20in%20the%20North.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHousing%20demand%20surged%20early%20in%20the%20pandemic%20%E2%80%94%20the%20country's%20homeowning%20ranks%20swelled%20by%20a%20whopping%202.2%20million%20people%20between%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202020%20and%20the%20same%20point%20in%202022%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20the%20Harvard%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies%20shows.%20But%20for%20all%20the%20talk%20of%20upheaval%2C%20movers%20more%20or%20less%20stuck%20to%20those%20pre-pandemic%20flight%20patterns%20%E2%80%94%20just%20at%20warp%20speed.%20People%20kept%20migrating%20from%20big-city%20centers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-7-americans-fled-cities-pandemic-cost-of-living-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eto%20the%20suburbs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20from%20the%20North%20to%20the%20South.%20Sun%20Belt%20states%2C%20including%20Florida%2C%20Texas%2C%20Arizona%2C%20and%20North%20Carolina%2C%20experienced%20the%20largest%20population%20gains%20from%20domestic%20migration%20between%20mid-2020%20and%20mid-2021%2C%20per%20a%20Harvard%20analysis%20of%20Census%20data.%20The%20Dallas%20metro%2C%20for%20example%2C%20gained%20around%2063%2C000%20people%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20that%20year%2C%20a%20huge%20jump%20from%20just%2019%2C000%20the%20year%20prior.%20Phoenix%2C%20Tampa%2C%20Austin%2C%20and%20Charlotte%20recorded%20similar%20increases.%20Expensive%20states%20with%20large%20urban%20areas%2C%20including%20California%2C%20New%20York%2C%20Illinois%2C%20and%20Massachusetts%2C%20saw%20the%20biggest%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20migration%20may%20follow%20long-held%20trends%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bnational%26quot%3B%20housing%20market%20is%20really%20a%20myth%20%E2%80%94%20every%20city%2C%20town%2C%20even%20ZIP%20code%2C%20has%20its%20own%20quirks.%20The%20chaotic%20reshuffle%20of%20the%20pandemic's%20early%20days%2C%20however%2C%20resulted%20in%20the%20closest%20thing%20we've%20seen%20to%20local%20markets%20around%20the%20country%20moving%20in%20the%20same%20direction%3A%20Prices%20went%20up%2C%20and%20inventory%20went%20down.%20Even%20if%20some%20states%20saw%20far%20more%20new%20arrivals%20than%20others%2C%20buyers%20all%20over%20the%20place%20jumped%20into%20the%20market%20in%20search%20of%20cheap%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20more%20space%2C%20and%20the%20promise%20of%20generational%20wealth%2C%20even%20if%20the%20move%20was%20just%20down%20the%20street.%20This%20led%20to%20higher%20prices%20practically%20across%20the%20board%20(with%20the%20exception%20of%20big%20cities%20that%20lost%20a%20ton%20of%20people%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-doom-loop-fix-american-city-housing-transit-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20San%20Francisco%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Now%2C%20though%2C%20the%20country%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-home-prices-falling-cities-cut-buying-a-home-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esplitting%20into%20two%20distinct%20markets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20someone's%20looking%20to%20sell%20a%20home%20these%20days%2C%20their%20prospects%20look%20a%20lot%20different%20depending%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-california-idaho-went-back-cost-of-living-weather-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhether%20they're%20in%20Boise%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Buffalo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Sun%20Belt%20and%20Mountain%20West%2C%20homebuilders%20saw%20the%20demand%20signals%20from%20the%20national%20moving%20moment%20and%20got%20busy.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20herd%20mentality%2C%20for%20sure%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ryan%20McKeveny%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20housing%20research%20firm%20Zelman%2C%20a%20Walker%20%26amp%3B%20Dunlop%20company.%20Homebuilders%2C%20he%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20gravitate%20to%20the%20same%20exact%20markets.%26quot%3B%20The%20Census%20estimates%20that%20the%20housing%20stock%20in%20the%20South%20region%20surged%20by%20almost%203.3%20million%20between%202020%20and%202024%2C%20compared%20to%20just%20750%2C000%20in%20the%20Midwest%20and%20a%20measly%20483%2C000%20in%20the%20Northeast.%20Despite%20the%20rush%20to%20break%20ground%2C%20those%20homes%20didn't%20materialize%20all%20at%20once.%20It%20usually%20takes%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20for%20new%20homes%20to%20crop%20up.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20prices%20in%20the%20Sun%20Belt%20spiked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustin-home-prices-falling-texas-mortgage-rates-housing-crisis-success-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETake%20Austin%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Texas%20capital%20was%20the%20fastest-growing%20large%20metropolitan%20area%20from%202020%20to%202022%2C%20Census%20data%20shows%2C%20adding%20a%20net%20120%2C000%20people%20for%20a%20population%20increase%20of%205.3%25.%20Even%20with%20a%20surge%20in%20homebuilding%2C%20supply%20simply%20could%20not%20keep%20up%3A%20The%20typical%20home%20price%20in%20Austin%20jumped%20by%20more%20than%2060%25%20in%20that%20same%20time%20period%2C%20Zillow%20found.%20Eventually%2C%20though%2C%20the%20builders%20made%20up%20some%20ground.%20By%20last%20fall%2C%20Austin's%20for-sale%20housing%20stock%20had%20climbed%20by%20more%20than%2076%2C000%20units%2C%20or%208.34%25%2C%20since%202020%2C%20Parcl%20Labs%20found%2C%20a%20monumental%20feat%20for%20a%20city%20that%20large.%20At%20the%20same%20time%20these%20new%20units%20came%20onto%20the%20market%2C%20however%2C%20the%20flow%20of%20people%20to%20Austin%20started%20to%20abate.%20Net%20domestic%20migration%20totaled%20less%20than%2014%2C000%20from%20mid-2023%20to%20mid-2024%2C%20still%20positive%20but%20well%20below%20the%20high%20of%2044%2C000%20in%202021.%20Buyers%20were%20also%20pulling%20back%20in%20the%20face%20of%20higher%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20which%20translate%20into%20vastly%20more%20expensive%20monthly%20payments.%20Fewer%20buyers%2C%20more%20homes%20up%20for%20sale%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20imagine%20what%20happens%20next.%20Austin%20home%20values%20have%20dropped%20more%20than%2023%25%20from%20their%20peak%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20Zillow%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20Zelman%20analysis%20shows%20that%20pandemic-era%20hot%20spots%20like%20Denver%2C%20Austin%2C%20Memphis%2C%20Tampa%2C%20and%20Dallas%20have%20seen%20big%20upticks%20in%20active%20inventory%2C%20or%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20available%20for%20sale%2C%20while%20median%20prices%20are%20down%20year%20over%20year.%20In%20Denver%2C%20for%20example%2C%20inventory%20is%20up%20almost%2050%25%20from%20the%20same%20point%20in%202019%2C%20while%20the%20median%20price%20is%20down%20slightly%20from%20a%20year%20ago.%20Dallas%20prices%20are%20down%20almost%202%25%20year-over-year%2C%20while%20inventory%20is%20up%20more%20than%2020%25%20from%202019.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-home-price-drops-insurance-real-estate-trend-sales-market-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENet%20migration%20to%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Texas%20remains%20positive%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Zelman%20analysis%2C%20but%20is%20lower%20than%20in%202019.%20The%20Dallas%20metro%20added%20just%2025%2C000%20people%20via%20domestic%20migration%20in%20the%2012-month%20period%20ending%20June%202024%2C%20down%20from%2091%2C000%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20prior.%20Tampa's%20increase%20of%2011%2C000%20was%20a%20fraction%20of%20its%2054%2C000-person%20gain%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20relocation%20bonanza.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20comedown%20from%20the%20pandemic-era%20frenzy%20may%20not%20come%20as%20a%20surprise.%20More%20interesting%20are%20the%20markets%20where%20sellers%20undeniably%20have%20the%20upper%20hand.%20These%20metros%20in%20the%20Northeast%20and%20Midwest%20mostly%20weren't%20subject%20to%20the%20huge%20price%20run-ups%20that%20were%20commonplace%20in%20the%20Sun%20Belt%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20get%20a%20ton%20of%20new%20supply%20from%20homebuilders%2C%20either%20%E2%80%94%20those%20guys%20were%20focused%20on%20carving%20out%20new%20home%20communities%20down%20south.%20Inventory%20levels%20in%20places%20like%20Buffalo%2C%20Milwaukee%2C%20Detroit%2C%20and%20Cleveland%20are%20still%20below%20their%202019%20watermarks%2C%20per%20Zelman's%20analysis%2C%20while%20prices%20have%20increased%20by%20anywhere%20from%204%25%20to%208%25%20compared%20to%20a%20year%20ago.%20People%20aren't%20exactly%20rushing%20to%20move%20to%20these%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20that%20the%20decades%20of%20migration%20losses%20have%20seriously%20slowed.%20The%20Cleveland%20metro%20lost%20just%203%2C500%20people%20on%20net%20in%202024%2C%20compared%20to%20nearly%2010%2C000%20in%202021.%20Same%20story%20in%20Milwaukee.%20The%20Minneapolis-St.%20Paul%20metro%20notched%20a%20slight%20%3Cem%3Eincrease%3C%2Fem%3E%20last%20year%20after%20bleeding%20a%20whopping%2014%2C000%20residents%20via%20net%20domestic%20migration%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20North-to-South%20movement%20still%20holds%2C%20but%20the%20North%20is%20losing%20fewer%20people%2C%20and%20the%20South%20isn't%20gaining%20like%20it%20once%20was.%20The%20most%20recent%20numbers%2C%20for%20the%20yearlong%20period%20ending%20in%20mid-2024%2C%20show%20net%20domestic%20migration%20to%20the%20South%20was%20down%20almost%2038%25%20compared%20to%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20Domestic%20migration%20to%20the%20Midwest%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20up%20about%2060%25%20in%20that%20same%20period%2C%20though%20it's%20still%20negative%20in%20absolute%20terms.%20The%20Northeast's%20net%20loss%20was%20down%20to%20192%2C000%20in%20the%20latest%20tally%2C%20compared%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20390%2C000%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20With%20the%20migration%20tide%20receding%2C%20sellers%20in%20once-hot%20metros%20are%20getting%20real.%20In%20Denver%2C%20Charlotte%2C%20Jacksonville%2C%20and%20a%20smattering%20of%20other%20Sun%20Belt%20markets%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20single-family%20homes%20for%20sale%20have%20seen%20a%20price%20cut%2C%20Parcl%20Labs%20data%20shows.%20In%20the%20Boston%2C%20Philadelphia%2C%20and%20Buffalo%20metros%2C%20the%20share%20of%20listings%20in%20that%20bucket%20drops%20to%20fewer%20than%20a%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20just%20one%20metric.%20To%20gauge%20sellers'%20desperation%20these%20days%2C%20Parcl%20Labs%20created%20what%20it%20calls%20the%20Motivated%20Sellers%20Index%2C%20which%20combines%20four%20factors%3A%20the%20number%20of%20price%20cuts%20on%20home%20listings%2C%20the%20time%20in%20between%20those%20cuts%2C%20the%20size%20of%20the%20price%20decreases%2C%20and%20the%20length%20of%20time%20homes%20are%20spending%20on%20the%20market.%20The%20higher%20the%20score%2C%20the%20greater%20the%20homeowners'%20urgency%20to%20sell.%20The%20lower%20half%20of%20the%20US%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20much%20of%20California%2C%20is%20awash%20in%20high%20scores%2C%20indicating%20sellers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-now-could-be-good-time-to-buy-house-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eceding%20negotiating%20power%20to%20buyers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Same%20goes%20for%20much%20of%20the%20West.%20The%20Midwest%20and%20Northeast%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20registered%20some%20of%20the%20lowest%20scores%20in%20the%20nation%3A%20Sellers%20there%20are%20sitting%20pretty%20by%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F0Irge%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Choropleth%20map%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F0Irge%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20declining%20home%20prices%20in%20many%20of%20these%20pandemic-winning%20housing%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20Jason%20Lewris%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20Parcl%20Labs%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20sellers%20in%20many%20of%20those%20markets%20are%20very%20motivated%20to%20get%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20index%2C%20Lewris%20says%2C%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20good%20proxy%20for%20where%20home%20prices%20may%20go.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20an%20abundance%20of%20motivated%20sellers%20today%20likely%20spells%20more%20price%20drops%20in%20the%20future.%20If%20homeowners%20are%20dropping%20their%20prices%20to%20meet%20the%20market%2C%20it%20shows%20they're%20not%20just%20testing%20the%20waters%20and%20hoping%20to%20get%20their%20dream%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fn4V2B%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Bar%20Chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fn4V2B%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202024%2C%20sellers%20appeared%20content%20to%20hold%20out%20for%20top%20dollar.%20This%20past%20summer%2C%20though%2C%20marked%20a%20notable%20uptick%20in%20seller%20motivation%2C%20says%20Lucy%20Ferguson%2C%20another%20executive%20at%20Parcl%20Labs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20only%20is%20there%20more%20stuff%20on%20the%20market%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20lot%20more%20price%20cutting%2C%26quot%3B%20Ferguson%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20like%20sellers%20meeting%20reality.%20That's%20the%20big%20theme.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-mortgage-rate-buydown-points-real-estate-prices-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%20still%20well%20above%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20pandemic-era%20lows%2C%20millions%20of%20households%20are%20playing%20the%20waiting%20game.%20Existing%20homeowners%20are%20unwilling%20(or%20unable)%20to%20give%20up%20their%20plum%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20so%20they're%20delaying%20moves%20that%20they'd%20otherwise%20be%20making.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-rich-renters-not-buying-home-price-new-apartment-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERenters%20are%20hanging%20tight%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20the%20affordability%20math%20tilts%20in%20their%20favor.%20This%20helps%20explain%20why%20the%20relative%20level%20of%20demand%20is%20so%20much%20higher%20across%20the%20Midwest%20than%20somewhere%20like%20Texas%20or%20Florida.%20When%20people%20are%20stuck%20in%20place%2C%20the%20typical%20migration%20patterns%20break%20down.%20The%20South%20adds%20fewer%20new%20buyers%2C%20and%20the%20North%20holds%20onto%20more%20of%20them.%20The%20result%20is%20weaker%20price%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20falling%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20in%20places%20that%20were%20once%20dependable%20strongholds%20of%20rising%20home%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20a%20young%20family%20in%20suburban%20Chicago%20or%20upstate%20New%20York%2C%20I%20would%20have%20bought%20my%20house%20from%20the%20guy%20who%20moved%20to%20Orlando%2C%26quot%3B%20Simonsen%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20didn't%20sell%2C%20and%20I%20still%20need%20to%20buy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20labor%20market%20also%20points%20to%20a%20stuck-in-place%20economy.%20Unemployment%20is%20low%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-hiring-unemployment-labor-force-participation-immigration-tariffs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehiring%20is%20way%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%26quot%3Bquits%20rate%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20percentage%20of%20workers%20voluntarily%20walking%20away%20from%20their%20jobs%2C%20is%20lagging.%20People%20are%20wary%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-purchases-financial-risks-economic-uncertainty-real-estate-careers-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emaking%20big%20life%20moves%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20leave%20them%20in%20the%20lurch%20if%20things%20go%20wrong.%20To%20look%20for%20signs%20of%20thawing%20in%20the%20housing%20market%2C%20Simonsen%20tells%20me%20he'll%20be%20watching%20for%20a%20pickup%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-changing-rto-pay-performance-reviws-want-you-to-quit-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20quits%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20if%20people%20are%20confident%20that%20they%20can%20leave%20their%20job%20and%20find%20a%20new%20one%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20sign%20that%20they're%20up%20for%20other%20major%20changes%20like%20a%20cross-country%20move.%20Until%20then%2C%20expect%20this%20reversal%20of%20the%20Covid-era%20winners%20and%20losers%20to%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20markets%20where%20home%20prices%20are%20kind%20of%20flat%20to%20lower%2C%20I%20don't%20exactly%20see%20a%20reason%20why%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20home%20prices%20are%20going%20to%20reaccelerate%20meaningfully%2C%26quot%3B%20McKeveny%2C%20the%20researcher%20at%20Zelman%2C%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sun%20Belt%20is%20still%20a%20long%20way%20from%20%26quot%3Bmarket%20crash%26quot%3B%20territory%20%E2%80%94%20even%20places%20like%20Austin%20are%20still%20adding%20people%20on%20a%20net%20basis%2C%20albeit%20at%20a%20much%20slower%20pace.%20But%20the%20price%20cuts%20represent%20a%20serious%20reality%20check.%20With%20the%20rise%20of%20Zoomtowns%20now%20a%20distant%20memory%2C%20buyers%20across%20the%20South%20and%20Mountain%20West%20benefit%20from%20more%20bargaining%20power%20than%20they've%20had%20in%20years.%20Their%20counterparts%20up%20north%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20still%20face%20stiff%20competition%20and%20rising%20prices.%20You%20can%20count%20on%20the%20pendulum%20to%20swing%20in%20the%20other%20direction%20once%20people%20start%20moving%20again.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20places%20like%20Cleveland%20and%20Buffalo%20will%20continue%20to%20enjoy%20prime%20position%20atop%20the%20housing-market%20heap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20correspondent%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzoomtowns-real-estate-price-cuts-housing-market-winners-midwest-northeast-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1761122041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f7ce951c1f80efbec5fca0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business