mated%20that%20around%2019%2C626%20of%2021%2C028%20total%20ICE%20employees%20would%20continue%20working%20either%20with%20or%20without%20pay%20until%20the%20shutdown%20ends.%20Similarly%2C%20around%2063%2C243%20of%20CBP's%2067%2C792%20workers%20were%20expected%20to%20be%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20funds%20to%20pay%20DHS%20workers%20are%20being%20drawn%20from%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F119th-congress%2Fhouse-bill%2F1%2Ftext%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Big%20Beautiful%20Bill%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20department%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20law%20allocates%20billions%20toward%20%26quot%3Bactivities%20in%20support%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security's%20mission%20to%20safeguard%20the%20borders%20of%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20available%20between%202025%20and%202029.%20The%20move%20to%20pay%20employees%20during%20the%20shutdown%20comes%20alongside%20the%20administration's%20deployment%20of%20ICE%20agents%20to%20US%20cities%2C%20such%20as%20Chicago%20and%20Portland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBobby%20Kogan%2C%20the%20senior%20director%20of%20federal%20budget%20policy%20at%20the%20left-leaning%20Center%20for%20American%20Progress%2C%20likened%20the%20usage%20of%20that%20funding%20to%20keep%20paying%20workers%20to%20the%20agencies%20having%20a%20credit%20card%20that%20doesn't%20expire%20until%202029%2C%20with%20very%20broad%20funding%20language%20from%20the%20legislation%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-pay-housing-college-education-benefits-signing-bonus%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMilitary%20personnel%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20began%20receiving%20paychecks%20in%20mid-October.%20Trump%20approved%20the%20White%20House%20and%20Pentagon%20to%20use%20funds%20left%20over%20for%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year%20for%20payroll%2C%20likely%20from%20the%20standard%20research%20and%20development%20testing%20and%20evaluation%20budget.%20The%20administration%20did%20not%20provide%20more%20information%20on%20what%20funding%20is%20specifically%20being%20used%20or%20how%20long%20that%20money%20will%20last%2C%20and%20Congress%20has%20not%20greenlit%20troop%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20such%20a%20dire%20circumstance%20as%20this%2C%20where%20there%20is%20no%20other%20appropriation%20providing%20for%20payment%20of%20military%20salaries%2C%20and%20where%20failure%20to%20pay%20our%20troops%20directly%20undercuts%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20other%20appropriations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20White%20House%20wrote%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Ff%2F%3Fid%3D00000199-f9bb-d346-aff9-fbbf1a8d0000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOctober%2017%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20lawmakers.%20%26quot%3BThe%20President%20may%2C%20as%20Commander%20in%20Chief%2C%20direct%20that%20such%20appropriations%20be%20used%20to%20cover%20military%20salaries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20past%20shutdowns%2C%20legislation%20has%20specifically%20passed%20either%20ahead%20of%20or%20during%20other%20funding%20lapses%20that%20stipulated%20troops%20would%20be%20paid.%20This%20time%20around%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20bipartisan%20entreaties%20from%20lawmakers%20to%20pass%20legislation%20%E2%80%94%20the%20administration%20unilaterally%20decided%20that%20troops%20would%20be%20paid%2C%20a%20move%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2025%2F10%2F20%2Ftroops-showdown-trump-funding-00614874%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estoked%20some%20ire%20among%20lawmakers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233191162-2e1d-497b-88a7-32b3ae193ede%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmployees%20at%20most%20agencies%20are%20furloughed%20or%20working%20without%20pay%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20government%20ceased%20normal%20operations%20on%20October%201%2C%20Business%20Insider%20has%20spoken%20with%20over%20two%20dozen%20federal%20wor